        "listening"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-the-graveyard-of-failed",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your first product failure isn't a failure. It's tuition. You just paid for a masterclass.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "learning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-first-product-failure",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Failure is not the opposite of success. It's part of it.",
      "author": "Arianna Huffington",
      "author_slug": "huffington",
      "categories": [
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "success"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "huffington-failure-is-not-the",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every mistake is a lesson. Every lesson makes you better. Fail fast, learn faster.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "learning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-every-mistake-is-a",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to learn is to fail. The second best is to learn from someone else's failure.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "learning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your biggest growth comes from your biggest failures. Embrace them.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "growth"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-biggest-growth-comes",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best entrepreneurs are the ones who can fail gracefully and come back stronger.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business",
        "entrepreneur"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "resilience"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-entrepreneurs-are",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your first failure is your most expensive lesson. Make it count.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "lesson"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-first-failure-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to handle failure is to expect it. Plan for it. Learn from it. Move on.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "planning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every failed product teaches you something that no successful product could.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business",
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "learning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-every-failed-product-teaches",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to recover from failure is to start something new immediately. Don't let the failure define you.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "resilience"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your reputation is built on how you handle failure, not how you handle success.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "reputation",
        "failure"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-reputation-is-built",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to learn from failure is to write about it. Your future self will thank you.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "documentation"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every failed startup is a case study. Every successful startup is a survivorship bias.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "bias"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-every-failed-startup-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to learn from failure is immediately after it happens. Not years later.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
